Hurry up.

101
00:15:50,225 --> 00:15:51,157
Yes.

102
00:16:12,781 --> 00:16:13,975
Well, Mr. Kurosaki!

103
00:16:15,584 --> 00:16:17,051
It's been a while.

104
00:16:17,152 --> 00:16:19,552
I was wondering if you could
arrange a recording.

105
00:16:20,289 --> 00:16:22,280
Your wrist is healed then?

106
00:16:22,824 --> 00:16:23,984
It's not for me.

107
00:16:24,092 --> 00:16:25,957
It's for this lady here.

108
00:16:26,061 --> 00:16:28,086
She's a student of yours?

109
00:16:28,463 --> 00:16:31,261
That's right. I guarantee her talent.

110
00:16:31,366 --> 00:16:33,527
Please arrange the session.

111
00:16:39,741 --> 00:16:43,404
Mr. Kurosaki,
isn't this woman a robot?

112
00:16:44,479 --> 00:16:47,778
What does it matter
if she's a robot?

113
00:16:47,883 --> 00:16:50,875
I've never heard of
a robot debuting.

114
00:16:51,553 --> 00:16:55,421
Her talent nearly matches mine.

115
00:16:55,524 --> 00:16:57,685
I have full confidence in her.

116
00:16:58,694 --> 00:16:59,956
But, I can't...

117
00:17:00,062 --> 00:17:04,465
The Goldberg variations!
I want her to start big!

118
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:06,158
Wait a minute.

119
00:17:07,135 --> 00:17:08,363
However good she is...

120
00:17:08,470 --> 00:17:11,735
