company. There are others.

125
00:17:23,919 --> 00:17:24,715
Let's go, Yuna.

126
00:17:33,895 --> 00:17:37,296
If you just listen to her,
you'll understand.

127
00:17:37,399 --> 00:17:39,060
Please give her an audition.

128
00:17:39,568 --> 00:17:40,728
Mr. Kurosaki...

129
00:17:40,836 --> 00:17:42,895
I have a reputation to uphold.

130
00:17:43,005 --> 00:17:48,136
There's no way I'm going to
record a robot performance.

131
00:17:49,778 --> 00:17:52,576
What's the difference between
robots and humans?

132
00:17:52,681 --> 00:17:56,117
How dare you. We owe a debt
of gratitude to robots.

133
00:17:56,785 --> 00:17:59,583
It's all right, Seiji.
Let's just go home.

134
00:18:00,322 --> 00:18:04,725
I'm not giving up.
You're going to have your debut.

135
00:18:05,627 --> 00:18:06,559
Yuna?

136
00:18:06,962 --> 00:18:11,194
You sure have strange interests,
Mr. Kurosaki. A robot?

137
00:18:12,501 --> 00:18:13,763
Yuna!

138
00:18:15,203 --> 00:18:16,397
Yuna!

139
00:18:23,612 --> 00:18:24,909
Where are you? Yuna!

140
00:18:32,587 --> 00:18:34,487
Where are you?!

141
00:18:46,768 --> 00:18:49,236
